<div id="pf4c" class="pf w0 h4" data-page-no="4c"><div class="pc pc4c w0 h4"><img class="bi x0 y0 w1 h5" alt="" src="bg4c.png"/><div class="t mb1 x5a h12 y7d4 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 11 </div><div class="t m52 x77 h12 y910 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">î˜‰</div><div class="t m752 x53 h12 y911 ff3 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">September 5-11 </div><div class="t m1aa x31 h22 y912 ff3 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Guidelines </div><div class="t m753 x4a h22 y913 ff3 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to Christian Character </div><div class="t m754 x3d h23 y850 ff6 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath Afternoon </div><div class="t m17e x5a h16 y63c ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">READ FOR THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Titus 2:1-10. </div><div class="t m3b7 x98 h16 y7b7 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: &quot;Show yourself in all respects a model of </div><div class="t m1f4 x98 h16 y914 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">good deeds, and in your teaching show integrity, gravity, </div><div class="t m1f4 x98 h16 y915 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and sound speech that cannot be censured&quot; (Titus 2:7, 8, </div><div class="t m749 x98 h16 y916 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">RSV). </div><div class="t m2be x98 h16 y641 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">KEY THOUGHT: Christian character stems from fellowship </div><div class="t m273 x5a h16 y917 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with Christ that manifests itself in loving, loyal attitudes and </div><div class="t m32a x5a h16 y48b ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">deeds. </div><div class="t m755 x98 h16 y918 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CHRISTIAN BEHAVIOR is very much a part of sound </div><div class="t m756 x5a h16 y78 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">doctrine (Titus 2:1). Attitudes and behavior that God can </div><div class="t m9c x5a h16 y736 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accept are inseparably linked with holiness. We are not holy </div><div class="t m47a x5a h16 y737 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by nature; holiness (sanctification) is Christ&apos;s gift to us by the </div><div class="t m757 x5a h16 y738 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Holy Spirit (1 Peter 1:1, 2; 2 Thess. 2:13). Holiness is evi-</div><div class="t m758 x5a h16 y919 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">denced through Christlike living. </div><div class="t m1ee x5c h16 y73a ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The book of Hebrews speaks of &quot;holiness, without which </div><div class="t m759 x5a h16 y73b ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">no man shall see the Lord&quot; (Heb. 12:14). Holiness is righteous-</div><div class="t m10f x5a h16 y91a ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ness. (See </div><div class="t m75a x87 h14 y73c ff5 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thoughts From the Mount of Blessing, </div><div class="t m5e7 x79 h16 y64d ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 18.) Right-</div><div class="t m516 x5a h16 y91b ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">eousness (holiness), as Jesus defined it in the Sermon on the </div><div class="t m2b0 x5a h16 y73e ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mount (Matthew 5), is a pure attitude of mind that manifests </div><div class="t m75b x5a h16 y91c ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">itself in outward acts acceptable to God. Paul taught that </div><div class="t m75c x5a h16 y73f ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ died, &quot;that the righteousness of the law might be ful-</div><div class="t m1ee x5a h16 y53d ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">filled in us&quot; (Rom. 8:3, 4). Christ within is righteousness or </div><div class="t md1 x5a h16 y91d ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">holiness within. The result is holy thoughts, words, and acts </div><div class="t m3ed x5a h16 y91e ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">directed by the Holy Spirit. </div><div class="t m75d x5a h16 y590 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">76 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
